22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c6a0586fcb546d2d4e396f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221589%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHDR%20TVs%2C%20like%20the%20LG%20G3%2C%20can%20produce%20images%20with%20enhanced%20contrast%20and%20colors.%3Cp%3ESteven%20Cohen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20dynamic%20range%20(HDR)%20is%20a%20feature%20that's%20supported%20on%20many%20new%20TVs%2C%20and%20it%20can%20provide%20a%20dramatic%20improvement%20in%20picture%20quality.%20HDR%20allows%20a%20display%20to%20produce%20images%20with%20higher%20brightness%2C%20better%20contrast%2C%20and%20more%20vivid%20colors.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20HDR%20can%20make%20images%20truly%20pop%20and%20appear%20more%20realistic%20and%20closer%20to%20how%20content%20creators%20intended%20for%20them%20to%20look.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20while%20HDR%20is%20now%20a%20common%20feature%20on%20all%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-tv%5C%22%3Ebest%20TVs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20performance%20varies%20greatly%20across%20different%20models.%20Just%20because%20a%20display%20says%20it%20supports%20HDR%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20capable%20of%20really%20taking%20advantage%20of%20the%20feature.%20To%20get%20the%20most%20impressive%20HDR%20viewing%20experience%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20focus%20on%20top%20OLED%20displays%2C%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-42039-20%26h%3D586a3eb847f68c44895637f8583d0be0d26ddf50847dcbf28680e8b2be3b2c5f%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f42c00%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Ftech%252Fwhat-is-hdr-tv%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSAMSUNG-65-Inch-Tracking-Q-Symphony-QN65S90C%252Fdp%252FB0BWFVBZM2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESamsung%20S90C%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20bright%20QLED%20sets%2C%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-42039-20%26h%3D67f6abf9af1e490c4d196dc6924325f8139d7779961177de2bd6b30c23eb1862%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f42c00%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Ftech%252Fwhat-is-hdr-tv%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FTCL-65QM850G-Accelerator-Streaming-Television%252Fdp%252FB0C1J4MPBB%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETCL%20QM8%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20you%20sort%20through%20all%20the%20ins%20and%20out%20of%20high%20dynamic%20range%20display%20technology%2C%20we've%20put%20together%20a%20handy%20guide%20detailing%20everything%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20HDR%20TVs%20and%20different%20HDR%20formats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20is%20HDR%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20HDR%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222866%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20scene%20featuring%20across%20a%20mountain%20range%20displayed%20on%20a%20Samsung%20S95C%20TV%20in%20a%20bright%20room.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c69a3943bb77284ba5a577%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222149%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20HDR%20video%20being%20displayed%20on%20a%20Samsung%20S95C%204K%20OLED%20TV.%3Cp%3ESteven%20Cohen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20dynamic%20range%20(HDR)%20is%20a%20display%20technology%20that%20enables%20a%20TV%20or%20monitor%20to%20produce%20enhanced%20contrast%20levels%20when%20playing%20an%20HDR-encoded%20video.%20This%20allows%20bright%20elements%20of%20an%20image%20to%20look%20brighter%20and%20dark%20elements%20to%20look%20darker%20while%20preserving%20more%20detail%20in%20all%20the%20steps%20between%20both%20ends%20of%20the%20spectrum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20enhanced%20contrast%20of%20HDR%20can%20create%20an%20added%20sense%20of%20depth%20with%20more%20visible%20details%20and%20realistic%20intensity%20in%20specular%20highlights%20and%20shadows.%20A%20good%20example%20would%20be%20a%20scene%20featuring%20sunlight%20glimmering%20off%20the%20ocean.%20Without%20HDR%2C%20a%20sequence%20like%20this%20could%20look%20comparatively%20dull%20with%20lost%20detail%20and%20blown-out%20highlights%2C%20but%20with%20the%20expanded%20range%20that%20HDR%20allows%2C%20extreme%20highlights%20like%20this%20are%20given%20room%20to%20breathe%20and%20really%20pop.%20The%20reflecting%20light%20can%20look%20more%20radiant%20and%20more%20detailed%20simultaneously.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrightness%20levels%20for%20HDR%20are%20measured%20in%20a%20unit%20called%20nits.%20The%20more%20nits%20a%20TV%20can%20produce%2C%20the%20brighter%20its%20HDR%20highlights%20can%20look.%20In%20general%2C%20most%20HDR%20movies%20and%20TV%20shows%20are%20mastered%20with%20a%20max%20of%201%2C000%20to%204%2C000%20nits%20in%20mind%2C%20though%20HDR%20formats%20can%20technically%20be%20mastered%20for%20up%20to%20a%20whopping%2010%2C000%20nits.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20no%20consumer%20displays%20available%20right%20now%20that%20can%20hit%20such%20a%20high%20number.%20Most%20premium%20HDR%20TVs%20currently%20max%20out%20at%20around%201%2C000%20to%202%2C500%20nits%2C%20while%20midrange%20models%20can%20achieve%20700%20to%201%2C000%20nits%2C%20and%20entry-level%20options%20offer%20around%20400%20to%20700%20nits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20is%20Wide%20Color%20Gamut%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20Wide%20Color%20Gamut%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHDR%20is%20often%20bundled%20with%20another%20display%20technology%20called%20Wide%20Color%20Gamut%20(WCG)%2C%20which%20enables%20a%20TV%20to%20produce%20an%20extended%20range%20of%20colors.%20Though%20technically%20two%20separate%20things%2C%20a%20wide%20color%20gamut%20is%20almost%20always%20used%20when%20mastering%20a%20video%20in%20HDR%2C%20so%20WCG%20is%20often%20considered%20part%20of%20HDR%20tech.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20using%20WCG%2C%20HDR%20videos%20are%20encoded%20within%20a%20color%20space%20called%20Rec.%202020%2C%20though%20most%20HDR%20movies%20and%20TV%20shows%20are%20actually%20graded%20for%20a%20narrower%20standard%20called%20DCI-P3.%20DCI-P3%20is%20the%20same%20range%20of%20colors%20used%20for%20modern%20digital%20theater%20projection%2C%20while%20Rec.%202020%20can%20offer%20an%20even%20wider%20range%20than%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20with%20HDR%20and%20WCG%2C%20you%20can%20enjoy%20the%20full%20spectrum%20of%20colors%20you%20see%20in%20theaters%20at%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20does%20HDR%20compare%20to%20SDR%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20HDR%20compare%20to%20SDR%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22HDR%20comparison%20Samsung%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e41cbaa4b661b4b1c3c5924%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHDR%20offers%20a%20big%20jump%20in%20contrast%20over%20SDR.%3Cp%3ESamsung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20industry's%20first%20consumer%20HDR%20displays%20hit%20the%20market%20in%202015%2C%20TVs%20were%20built%20to%20adhere%20to%20a%20standard%20dynamic%20range%20(SDR)%20specification.%20SDR%20displays%20and%20content%20are%20designed%20with%20a%20max%20of%20only%20100%20nits%20in%20mind%2C%20and%20they're%20typically%20produced%20for%20a%20limited%20color%20gamut%20called%20Rec.%20709.%20Compared%20to%20the%20DCI-P3%20color%20space%20used%20on%20most%20HDR%20videos%2C%20Rec.%20709%20offers%20a%20much%20more%20restricted%20gamut%20of%20colors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20SDR%20displays%20produce%20comparatively%20dim%20and%20low-contrast%20images%20with%20a%20narrower%20range%20of%20colors%20when%20put%20head-to-head%20with%20an%20HDR%20TV%20playing%20HDR%20programming.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20an%20SDR%20version%20of%20a%20movie%20or%20TV%20show%20will%20often%20look%20flat%20and%20washed%20out%20compared%20to%20its%20HDR%20counterpart.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESDR%20TVs%20in%20HD%20and%204K%20resolution%20are%20still%20manufactured%20today%2C%20and%20all%20HDR-compatible%20TVs%20can%20still%20display%20SDR%20signals%20accurately.%20While%20HDR%20mastering%20has%20become%20a%20popular%20choice%20for%20new%20streaming%20content%20and%204K%20Blu-ray%20movies%2C%20SDR%20is%20still%20the%20norm%20for%20cable%2C%20satellite%2C%20and%20over-the-air%20TV%20broadcasts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20do%20I%20watch%20HDR%20content%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20I%20watch%20HDR%20movies%20and%20TV%20shows%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20watch%20HDR%20videos%2C%20you%20need%20an%20HDR-capable%20display%20and%20access%20to%20HDR-encoded%20content.%20Every%20element%20in%20your%20home%20entertainment%20chain%20also%20has%20to%20support%20HDR%2C%20so%20if%20you%20watch%20videos%20through%20a%20streaming%20stick%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20HDR%20compatible%2C%20and%20if%20you%20connect%20your%20media%20player%20to%20your%20TV%20through%20an%20AV%20receiver%20or%20soundbar%2C%20those%20components%20need%20to%20support%20HDR%20passthrough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHDR%20videos%20are%20available%20on%20all%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-streaming-service%5C%22%3Ebest%20streaming%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20Disney%20Plus%2C%20Netflix%2C%20Hulu%2C%20and%20Amazon%20Prime%20Video.%20HDR%20is%20also%20used%20on%20most%204K%20Ultra%20HD%20Blu-ray%20discs.%20Some%20live%20sporting%20events%20are%20also%20broadcast%20in%20HDR%20through%20some%20providers%2C%20but%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20cable%2C%20satellite%2C%20and%20live%20TV%20streaming%20broadcasts%20are%20still%20presented%20in%20SDR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20should%20I%20look%20for%20in%20an%20HDR%20TV%3F%C2%A0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20should%20I%20look%20for%20in%20an%20HDR%20TV%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Waves%20crashing%20over%20rocks%20displayed%20on%20a%20TCL%20QM8%20TV%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65845863a79e5746976c337a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETCL's%20QM8%20delivers%20outstanding%20peak%20brightness%20to%20enable%20high-end%20HDR%20performance.%3Cp%3ERyan%20Waniata%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-4k-tv%5C%22%3Ebest%204K%20TVs%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20some%20level%20of%20HDR%20support%2C%20and%20you%20can%20even%20find%20some%20HDTVs%20with%20HDR%20capabilities%2C%20but%20performance%20can%20vary%20dramatically%20between%20cheaper%20models%20and%20more%20expensive%20displays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20best%20HDR%20performance%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20buy%20either%20an%20OLED%20TV%20or%20an%20LED%20display%20with%20local%20dimming%20and%20expanded%20colors.%20LED%20TVs%20with%20those%20features%20are%20often%20branded%20as%20QLED%2C%20Neo%20QLED%2C%20or%20QNED.%20All%20of%20these%20display%20options%20offer%20the%20necessary%20contrast%20control%2C%20peak%20brightness%2C%20and%20color%20capabilities%20that%20are%20needed%20to%20really%20show%20off%20the%20benefits%20of%20HDR%20playback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20brightness%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20choose%20a%20display%20model%20that%20comes%20close%20to%20outputting%201%2C000%20nits%20or%20higher%20to%20see%20the%20full%20benefits%20of%20HDR%20content.%20However%2C%20TVs%20with%20that%20level%20of%20performance%20tend%20to%20be%20a%20bit%20pricey%2C%20and%20you%20can%20still%20get%20worthwhile%20entry-level%20HDR%20performance%20out%20of%20cheaper%20models%20that%20max%20out%20in%20the%20500%20to%20600%20nits%20range.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20rundown%20of%20some%20of%20the%20top%204K%20HDR%20TVs%20that%20we%20recommend%2C%20from%20least%20to%20most%20expensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Are%20there%20different%20HDR%20formats%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20there%20different%20HDR%20formats%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20four%20primary%20HDR%20content%20formats%3A%20%3Cstrong%3EHDR10%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%3Cstrong%3EHDR10%2B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%3Cstrong%3EDolby%20Vision%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cstrong%3EHLG%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHDR10%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20the%20most%20basic%20and%20common%20HDR%20format.%20It's%20supported%20on%20all%20HDR%20TVs%20and%20is%20used%20as%20the%20standard%20HDR%20format%20on%20all%204K%20Ultra%20HD%20Blu-ray%20discs%20and%20streaming%20apps%20with%20HDR%20content.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20you%20can%20think%20of%20it%20as%20an%20HDR%20base%20layer%20that%20more%20advanced%20HDR%20formats%20can%20be%20added%20on%20top%20of.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHDR10%20videos%20can%20be%20mastered%20for%20a%20peak%20of%20up%20to%2010%2C000%20nits%2C%20though%20most%20HDR10%20content%20has%20been%20graded%20for%201%2C000-4%2C000%20nits.%20HDR10%20videos%20are%20encoded%20with%20information%20called%20%26quot%3Bstatic%20metadata.%26quot%3B%20This%20metadata%20tells%20a%20TV%20what%20colors%20to%20show%20and%20how%20bright%20the%20TV's%20images%20are%20supposed%20to%20look.%20Static%20metadata%20is%20a%20bit%20limited%2C%20however%2C%20as%20it%20can%20only%20provide%20information%20that%20addresses%20the%20video%20as%20a%20whole%20instead%20of%20each%20individual%20scene.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20HDR10%20movie%20is%20played%20on%20an%20HDR%20TV%20that%20can't%20support%20the%20full%20range%20of%20brightness%20and%20color%20that%20its%20metadata%20calls%20for%2C%20the%20display%20must%20adapt%20on%20its%20own%20to%20scale%20highlights%20and%20color%20volume%20to%20land%20within%20its%20capabilities.%20This%20kind%20of%20adjustment%20is%20called%20%26quot%3Btone%20mapping%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20different%20display%20manufacturers%20handle%20tone%20mapping%20differently.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20this%20can%20lead%20to%20issues%20with%20certain%20scenes%20in%20HDR10%20videos%20appearing%20too%20blown%20out%20or%20too%20dark%20since%20a%20TV's%20tone%20mapping%20may%20not%20match%20what%20a%20content%20creator%20intended.%20And%20this%20is%20where%20%3Cstrong%3EDolby%20Vision%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20%3Cstrong%3EHDR10%2B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20come%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDolby%20Vision%20and%20HDR10%2B%20are%20both%20%26quot%3Bdynamic%20metadata%26quot%3B%20HDR%20formats.%20This%20means%20that%20HDR%20brightness%20and%20color%20information%20can%20be%20detailed%20on%20a%20scene-by-scene%20or%20even%20shot-by-shot%20basis.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Dolby%20Vision%20and%20HDR10%2B%20videos%20can%20provide%20more%20detailed%20tone%20mapping%20instructions%20to%20a%20TV%20so%20that%20the%20creators'%20original%20intent%20is%20more%20accurately%20preserved.%20These%20formats%20are%20supported%20on%20select%20TVs%2C%20discs%2C%20and%20streaming%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20%3Cstrong%3EHLG%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20an%20HDR%20format%20that's%20used%20for%20TV%20broadcasts.%20This%20format%20does%20not%20use%20metadata%20at%20all%2C%20and%20it's%20backward%20compatible%20with%20SDR%20displays%2C%20so%20broadcasters%20can%20send%20an%20HLG%20signal%20to%20all%20customers%20and%20have%20it%20look%20correct%20on%20both%20SDR%20and%20HDR%20TVs.%20If%20an%20HDR%20TV%20broadcast%20were%20sent%20to%20an%20SDR%20TV%20using%20any%20of%20the%20other%20HDR%20formats%20we've%20discussed%2C%20it%20would%20display%20with%20inaccurate%20colors%20and%20contrast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Are%20Dolby%20Vision%20and%20HDR10%2B%20better%20than%20HDR10%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20Dolby%20Vis