0innovation%20at%20the%20New%20Lines%20Institute%2C%20said%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20following%20%E2%80%9Ca%20careful%20playbook%E2%80%9D%20to%20focus%20attacks%20against%20Iranian%20proxies%20in%20retaliation%20while%20refraining%20from%20preemptive%20strikes%20that%20might%20%E2%80%9Cgoad%20Iran%E2%80%9D%20into%20expanding%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20secondary%20goal%20that%20the%20US%20is%20trying%20to%20achieve%20with%20these%20strikes%20against%20key%20Iranian%20proxy%20leaders%20in%20Iraq%20is%20to%20send%20a%20strong%20message%20that%20these%20Iranian%20proxy%20figures%20cannot%20hide%20behind%20their%20affiliation%20with%20the%20Iraqi%20government%20to%20avoid%20retribution%20from%20America%2C%E2%80%9D%20Heras%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Iran%20and%20the%20militias%20it%20trains%20and%20supplies%2C%20however%2C%20have%20many%20reasons%20to%20resume%20their%20attacks%2C%20analysts%20say.%20For%20militias%20like%20Kataib%20Hezbollah%20in%20Iraq%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20to%20provoke%20US%20responses%20that%20increase%20opposition%20to%20the%202%2C500%20US%20troops%20based%20in%20Iraq.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20see%20it%2C%20especially%20in%20Iraq%2C%20where%20each%20new%20US%20retaliatory%20strike%20stirs%20up%20local%20opposition%20and%20forces%20the%20Baghdad%20government%20to%20ramp%20up%20its%20rhetoric%20about%20ending%20the%20US%20and%20Coalition%20presence%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lund%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBy%20responding%20to%20the%20attacks%2C%20the%20United%20States%20poisons%20its%20relationship%20with%20local%20allies%20and%20screws%20up%20its%20position%20in%20Iraq.%20But%20not%20responding%20is%20also%20not%20an%20option.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20the%20attacks%20will%20continue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Iran%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20much%20larger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELund%20believes%20Iran%20is%20trying%20to%20force%20the%20US%20into%20%E2%80%9Ca%20choice%20of%20either%20escalating%2C%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20serious