0for%20those%20found%20guilty%20of%20cheating%20or%20aiding%20in%20any%20form%20of%20irregularity.%20The%20bill%20sailed%20through%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20today%20with%20a%20voice%20vote%2C%20following%20its%20earlier%20approval%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20February%206th.%20Notably%2C%20amendments%20proposed%20by%20opposition%20members%20were%20rejected%20during%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20law%20sends%20a%20strong%20message%20against%20exam%20malpractices%2C%20aiming%20to%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20and%20ensure%20fair%20competition%20for%20all%20aspirants%20in%20crucial%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20aims%20to%20address%20dishonest%20actions%20and%20irregularities%20in%20competitive%20exams%20by%20imposing%20strict%20penalties.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20bill%20suggests%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20national%20technical%20committee%20on%20public%20examinations%20with%20the%20purpose%20of%20enhancing%20the%20security%20of%20computerized%20examination%20procedures.%20This%20committee%20will%20be%20responsible%20for%20providing%20recommendations%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20Features%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStiff%20Penalties%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20bill%20prescribes%20a%20maximum%20jail%20term%20of%2010%20years%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20those%20found%20guilty%20of%20cheating%20or%20aiding%20in%20cheating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETargets%20Organised%20Cheating%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20specifically%20targets%20individuals%20and%20institutions%20involved%20in%20organized%20cheating%20activities%2C%20like%20leaking%20question%20papers%20or%20tampering%20with%20answer%20sheets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProtects%20Meritocracy%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20aim%20is%20to%20deter%20unfair%20practices%20that%20undermine%20merit-based%20selection%20in%20competitive%20exams%2C%20ensuring%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20