%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.parliament.na%2Fdt_team%2Fgeingob-hage%2F%5C%22%3EAugust%203%2C%201941%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20joined%20the%20ranks%20of%20the%20national%20liberation%20movement%20South%20West%20African%20People%E2%80%99s%20Organisation%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sahistory.org.za%2Farticle%2Fsouth-west-africa-peoples-organisation-swapo%5C%22%3ESwapo%3C%2Fa%3E)%20during%20its%20formation%20in%201960.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20official%20statement%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNamPresidency%2Fstatus%2F1753963884828823682%5C%22%3Edeclared%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Namibian%20nation%20has%20lost%20a%20distinguished%20servant%20of%20the%20people%2C%20a%20liberation%20struggle%20icon%2C%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20our%20constitution%20and%20the%20pillar%20of%20the%20Namibian%20house.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Swapo%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20he%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FHage-Geingob%5C%22%3Eelected%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20Namibia%E2%80%99s%20president%20for%202015%20to%202020%20in%20November%202014.%20In%202017%20he%20replaced%20Hifikepunye%20Pohamba%20as%20party%20president.%20As%20head%20of%20state%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fnamibia-badly-needs-refurbishment-after-32-years-under-the-ruling-party-179205%5C%22%3Efar%20reaching%20executive%20powers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20remained%20in%20control%20over%20party%20and%20government%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeingob%E2%80%99s%20political%20career%20differed%20from%20that%20of%20his%20predecessors%20Sam%20Nujoma%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FHifikepunye-Pohamba%5C%22%3EHifikepunye%20Pohamba%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fallafrica.com%2Fstories%2F200904240652.html%5C%22%3ENujoma%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founding%20president%20of%20Swapo%2C%20served%20as%20president%20for%20three%20terms%20(1990-2005).%20Pohamba%20(2005-2015)%20was%20his%20designated%20successor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeingob%20personified%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F44508019%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cchanging%20of%20the%20guard%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20advanced%20formal%20education%20left%20an%20imprint%20on%20the%20way%20of%20governance%20during%20his%20terms%20in%20office.%20A%20younger%20generation%20moved%20gradually%20into%20higher%20party%20and%20state%20ranks.%20He%20successfully%20modified%20the%20heroic%20struggle%20narrative%20and%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20more%20inclusive%2C%20patriotic%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09183717%2FGeingob-Nujoma-Pohamba.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09183717%2FGeingob-Nujoma-Pohamba.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09183717%2FGeingob-Nujoma-Pohamba-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696426%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22559%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGeingob%2C%20Nujoma%20and%20Pohamba%20in%20Swapo%20colours.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40hagegeingob.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGeingob%E2%80%99s%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeingob%20had%20his%20cultural%20roots%20in%20the%20Damara%20community.%20This%20made%20him%20different%20from%20the%20mainstream%20Swapo%20leadership%2C%20which%20is%20mainly%20from%20the%20Oshiwambo-speaking%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeingob%E2%80%99s%20different%20background%20counted%20in%20his%20favour%20among%20many%20Namibians%20when%20campaigning%20for%20presidency.%20People%20welcomed%20a%20leader%20with%20origins%20in%20an%20ethnically%20defined%20minority%20group%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20multi-cultural%20plurality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.parliament.na%2Fdt_team%2Fgeingob-hage%2F%5C%22%3EStudying%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0at%20the%20US%20American%20Temple%20University%20in%20Philadelphia%2C%20the%20Fordham%20University%20(BA)%20and%20The%20New%20School%20(MA)%2C%20both%20in%20New%20York%2C%20Geingob%20was%20representing%20Swapo%20since%20the%20mid-1960s%20at%20the%20United%20Nations.%20In%201975%20he%20became%20the%20head%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F160803%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20Institute%20for%20Namibia%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20Lusaka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20returned%20to%20Namibia%20in%20mid-1989%2C%20leading%20the%20Swapo%20election%20campaign%20in%20the%20transition%20to%20independence%20under%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F40175168%5C%22%3Esupervision%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20played%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kas.de%2Fc%2Fdocument_library%2Fget_file%3Fuuid%3Da5fa370c-004f-c92d-0ba3-7b3ca48aab38%26groupId%3D252038%5C%22%3Edecisive%20role%20as%20chairman%20of%20the%20elected%20Constituent%20Assembly%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20appointed%20Prime%20Minister%20in%201990.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%20he%20fell%20into%20disgrace%20for%20not%20supporting%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hsrcpress.ac.za%2Fbooks%2Flegacies-of-power%5C%22%3ESam%20Nujoma%E2%80%99s%20presidency-for-life%20ambitions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%20of%20accepting%20his%20demotion%20to%20Minister%20of%20Regional%20and%20Local%20Government%20and%20Housing%2C%20he%20became%20executive%20secretary%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgcacma.org%2FAboutGCA.htm%5C%22%3EWashington-based%20Global%20Coalition%20for%20Africa%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202004%20he%20obtained%20a%20PhD%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Leeds%20for%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fetheses.whiterose.ac.uk%2F21090%2F%5C%22%3Ethesis%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20state%20formation%20in%20Namibia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20returned%20the%20same%20year%20to%20Namibia.%20Thanks%20to%20Pohamba%E2%80%99s%20reconciliatory%20approach%2C%20he%20made%20a%20remarkable%20comeback.%20Minister%20of%20Trade%20and%20industry%20from%202008%20to%202012%2C%20he%20again%20became%20Prime%20Minister%20(2012-2015).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20clever%20politically%20strategic%20mind%20paved%20the%20way%20to%20be%20elected%20as%20president%20of%20the%20party%20and%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGeingob%E2%80%99s%20presidency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Presidential%20and%20National%20Assembly%20elections%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmg.co.za%2Farticle%2F2014-12-02-namibias-swapo-win-elections-geingob-voted-as-president%2F%5C%22%3ENovember%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Geingob%20and%20Swapo%20scored%20the%20best%20results%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20history.%20While%20Nujoma%20was%20termed%20the%20president%20for%20stability%20and%20Pohamba%20the%20president%20for%20continuity%2C%20Geingob%20campaigned%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.co.za%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.10520%2FEJC-5ae9d1ff3%5C%22%3Epresident%20for%20prosperity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20made%20him%20the%20president%20of%20unfulfilled%20promises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeingob%E2%80%99s%20rhetoric%20disclosed%20a%20stronger%20contrast%20between%20what%20was%20said%20and%20what%20was%20done%20than%20that%20of%20his%20predecessors.%20He%20used%20more%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F03056244.2018.1500360%5C%22%3Epopulist%3C%2Fa%3E%20rhetoric%20as%20his%20style%20of%20governance%20and%20leadership%2C%20coining%20the%20metaphor%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CNamibian%20House%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20he%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.namibiaembassyusa.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fstatements%2FInaugural%2520Speech%2520by%2520HE%2520Hage%2520%2520Geingob%25201.pdf%5C%22%3Edeclared%20in%20his%20inaugural%20address%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20of%20us%20must%20play%20our%20part%20in%20the%20success%20of%20this%20beautiful%20house%20we%20call%20Namibia.%20We%20need%20to%20renew%20it%20from%20time%20to%20time%20by%20undergoing%20renovations%20and%20extensions.%20%E2%80%A6%20Let%20us%20stand%20together%20in%20building%20this%20new%20Namibian%20house%20in%20which%20no%20Namibian%20will%20feel%20left%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20over%20the%20years%20many%20felt%20left%20out.%20The%20November%202019%20parliamentary%20and%20presidential%20election%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F00358533.2020.1717090%5C%22%3Eresults%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0were%20the%20worst%20for%20Swapo%20since%20independence.%20A%202020%20Afrobarometer%20survey%20confirmed%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.afrobarometer.org%2Farticles%2Ftrust-political-institutions-decline-namibia-afrobarometer-survey-shows%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20decline%20of%20trust%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20fairness%2C%20Geingob%20entered%20office%20at%20a%20difficult%20time.%20The%20country%20faced%20fiscal%20constraints%20and%20a%20period%20of%20serious%20droughts%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20traumatic%20impact%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F00358533.2020.1790776%5C%22%3ECovid%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20socio-economic%20track%20record%20under%20him%20was%20at%20best%20mixed.%20On%20balance%2C%20his%20governance%20was%20characterised%20by%20a%20considerable%20gap%20between%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.namibian.com.na%2Fnamibia-2024-promises-or-delivery%2F%5C%22%3Epromises%20and%20delivery%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Geingob%20a%20decline%20of%20ethics%20became%20visible%2C%20manifested%20spectacularly%20in%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D_FJ1TB0nwHs%5C%22%3Ecorruption%20scandal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.namibian.com.na%2Ftimely-and-engaging-fishrot%2F%5C%22%3Efishing%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20became%20the%20synonym%20of%20state%20capture.%20Fighting%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fafrica.cgtn.com%2Fnamibias-president-geingob-pledges-stronger-fight-against-corruption%2F%5C%22%3Ecorruption%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0became%20Geingob%E2%80%99s%20mantra.%20But%20it%20had%20little%20credibility%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20wider%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20moderniser%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeingob%20was%20first%20married%20(1967-1992)%20to%20a%20strong-minded%20African-American%20woman.%20Fondly%20called%20%E2%80%9CAuntie%20Patty%E2%80%9D%2C%20Priscilla%20Geingos%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.namibiansun.com%2Fnews%2Fauntie-patty-laid-to-rest-in-windhoek%5C%22%3Elaid%20to%20rest%20in%20Windhoek%20in%202014%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20entering%20office%2C%20Geingob%20(divorced%20for%20a%20second%20time%20from%20Loini%20Kandume%20in%202008)%20married%20the%20businesswoman%20Monica%20Kalondo%20in%202015.%20Strong%2C%20loyal%2C%20and%20independent-minded%2C%20Monica%20Geingos%20became%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unaids.org%2Fen%2Faboutunaids%2Funaidsambassadors%2FMonicaGeingos%5C%22%3Eactive%20and%20internationally%20recognised%20First%20Lady%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20Geingob%E2%80%99s%20most%20laudable%20achievements%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fnews%2F2022%2F06%2Fexperts-committee-elimination-discrimination-against-women-congratulate-namibia%5C%22%3Eis%20a%20gender-aware%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20elevated%20Namibia%20into%20the%20league%20of%20countries%20with%20the%20highest%20proportion%20of%20women%20in%20leading%20political%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnamibia.unfpa.org%2Fen%2Ftopics%2Fgender-based-violence-3%5C%22%3Etook%20a%20stand%20against%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0gender-based%20violence%20and%20the%20country%20progressed%20in%20closing%20the%20gender%20inequality%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20reluctant%20to%20give%20in%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonblade.com%2F2023%2F06%2F14%2Flandmark-namibia-supreme-court-ruling-sparks-anti-gay-backlash%2F%5C%22%3Ehomophobia%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0prevalent%20among%20parliamentarians.%20In%20May%202023%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.namibian.com.na%2Fon-same-sex-relationships%2F%5C%22%3Eequal%20treatment%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20two%20foreign%20same%20sex%20spouses%20married%20to%20Namibian%20citizens.%20While%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20members%20of%20the%20National%20Assembly%20pushed%20through%20a%20law%20amendment%20seeking%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.southernafricalitigationcentre.org%2F2023%2F07%2F20%2Fnamibias-proposed-amendment-of-the-marriage-act-an-attack-on-the-rule-of-law-and-the-judiciary%2F%5C%22%3Eto%20invalidate%20the%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Geingob%20did%20not%20sign%20the%20bill%20into%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGeingob%E2%80%99s%20legacy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20last%20official%20statements%20by%20Geingob%2C%20on%20January%2013%2C%202024%2C%20testified%20to%20his%20strong%20views.%20Upset%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnamibia-germany-israel-south-africa-gaza%5C%22%3EGermany%E2%80%99s%20taking%20side%20with%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNamPresidency%2Fstatus%2F1746259880871149956%5C%22%3Efumed%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20German%20Government%20is%20yet%20to%20fully%20atone%20for%20the%20genocide%20it%20committed%20on%20Namibian%20soil.%20Germany%20cannot%20morally%20express%20commitment%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20Convention%20against%20genocide%2C%20including%20atonement%20for%20the%20genocide%20in%20Namibia%2C%20whilst%20supporting%20the%20equivalent%20of%20a%20holocaust%20and%20genocide%20in%20Gaza.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeingob%20was%20ambitious%20to%20enter%20Namibian%20history%20as%20the%20president%20who%20did%20more%20to%20promote%20the%20welfare%20and%20advancement%20of%20citizens.%20But%20he%20struggled%20to%20turn%20that%20vision%20into%20reality%20in%20office.%20Namibia%20remains%20among%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldbank.org%2Fen%2Fcountry%2Fnamibia%2Foverview%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DNamibia%2520ranks%2520as%2520one%2520of%2Cservices%2520are%2520large%2520and%2520widening%5C%22%3Emost%20unequal%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20reiterated%20in%20his%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNamPresidency%2Fstatus%2F1741615241614508304%5C%22%3ENew%20Year%20Address%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20order%20to%20seize%20the%20opportunities%20that%20are%20in%20line%20with%20our%20ambitions%20and%20expectations%2C%20we%20should%20redouble%20our%20efforts%20to%20make%20Namibia%20a%20better%20country.%20I%20call%20on%20each%20one%20of%20you%20to%20work%20harder%20for%20our%20collective%20welfare.%20I%20call%20on%20all%20of%20you%20to%20hold%20hands%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20no%20one%20feels%20left%20out%20of%20the%20Namibian%20House.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20legacy%20as%20a%20moderniser%20will%20live%20on%20despite%20all%20the%20contradictions%20and%20unfulfilled%20promises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHamba%20kahle%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Rest%20in%20peace).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHenning%20Melber%2C%20Extraordinary%20Professor%2C%20Department%20of%20Political%20Sciences%2C%20University%20of%20Pret