0Govt%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Surgical%20Strike'%20on%20Black%20Money%2C%20Missing%20in%20Centre's%20White%20Paper.%20As%20Are%20Jobs.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09162420%2Fimage.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20on%20Thursday%20(February%208)%20tabled%20a%20white%20paper%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20detailing%20how%20it%20had%20restored%20the%20health%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfragile%20state%E2%80%9D%20which%20it%20had%20inherited%20from%20the%20UPA%20years%2C%20the%20document%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20its%20demonetisation%20exercise%2C%20which%20was%20described%20at%20the%20time%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F822685%2Fdemonetisation-a-surgical-strike-by-on-black-money-has-hit-terror-funding-manohar-parrikar%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Csurgical%20strike%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20black%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20missing%20from%20the%20comparative%20analysis%20of%20performance%20between%20the%20UPA%20and%20NDA%20years%20is%20employment%20and%20jobs%2C%20presumably%20because%20the%20data%20suggests%20the%20past%20decade%20has%20not%20been%20a%20good%20one%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20job%20creation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202016%20demonetisation%20decision%2C%20which%20was%20announced%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20to%20tackle%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdisease%20of%20black%20money%E2%80%9D%2C%20led%20to%20countrywide%20hardship%2C%20especially%20for%20the%20poor%20and%20those%20living%20in%20rural%20India.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fthe-costs-of-demonetisation-death-toll-rises-to-82-eight-million-bidi-workers-remain-unpaid%5C%22%3Eone%20month%20since%20the%20decision%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20media%20reported%20that%2082%20people%20had%20died%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%2059-page%20White%20Paper%20presented%20in%20parliament%20on%20Thursday%C2%A0%20on%20the%20Indian%20Economy%E2%80%99%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20this%20%E2%80%98notebandi%E2%80%99.%20It%20details%20the%20list%20of%20corruption%20scams%20by%20the%20UPA%20government%20between%202004%20and%202014%2C%20but%20does%20not%20mention%20how%20demonetisation%20helped%20tackle%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdisease%20of%20black%20money%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20missing%2C%20terms%20like%20%E2%80%98cash%20in%20circulation%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20term%20black%20money%20finds%20mention%20only%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20continue%20to%20undertake%20measures%20to%20unearth%20black%20money%20and%20to%20discourage%20recourse%20to%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fhow-the-black-money-was-brought-back-to-india%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Black%20Money%20Was%20Brought%20Back%20to%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20does%2C%20however%2C%20give%20a%20list%20of%20corruption%20cases%20under%20the%20UPA%20and%20says%20%E2%80%9Cdecision-making%20came%20to%20a%20standstill%20due%20to%20corruption%20and%20scandals%20in%20defence%20%2C%20compromising%20defence%20preparedness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98black%20paper%E2%80%99%20that%20was%20also%20released%20on%20Thursday%2C%20hours%20before%20the%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20white%20paper%2C%20demonetisation%20does%20find%20mention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSeven%20years%20after%20PM%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20disastrous%20demonetisation%2C%20the%20economic%20effects%20continued%20to%20haunt%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20document%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%9910%20Saal%20Anyay%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNone%20of%20the%20ever-changing%20goals%20of%20the%20exercise%20have%20been%20met.%20Black%20money%20remains%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20demonetisation%20affected%20it.%20Corruption%20abounds%20as%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%2040%25%20sarkar%20in%20Karnataka%20showed.%20The%20country%20did%20not%20even%20become%20cashless.%20Cash%20in%20circulation%20has%20increased%20between%202016%C2%A0%20and%202023%3B%20%5Bit%5D%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%20from%20Rs%2016%20lakh%20crore%20in%202016%20to%20Rs%2034%20lakh%20crore%20in%202023.%20The%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20data%20showed%20that%20from%20October%20to%20January%2019%2C%20currency%20leakage%20from%20bank%20deposits%20to%20cash%20was%20as%20much%20as%20Rs%201.2%20lakh%20crore.%20As%20a%20share%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20GDP%2C%20cash%20has%20increased%20to%2012.7%25%20in%202023%20from%2011.6%25%20in%20March%202014.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20costs%20of%20this%20blunder%20were%20severe.%20More%20than%2015%20lakh%20jobs%20were%20estimated%20to%20be%20lost%20in%20the%20first%20four%20months%20of%202017%2C%20mainly%20in%20small%20businesses%20and%20the%20informal%20sector.%20Over%20a%20hundred%20people%20died%20standing%20in%20line%20to%20change%20bank%20notes.%20The%20Modi%20government%20has%20still%20not%20learnt%20the%20lesson%20%E2%80%93%20the%20scrapping%20of%20Rs%202%2C000%20note%20is%20yet%20another%20painful%20reminder%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20while%20hearing%2058%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20decision%2C%20held%20that%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-demonetisation-judgment-nagarathna%5C%22%3Evalid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20ruling%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%2C%20authored%20by%20Justice%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20said%20that%20demonetisation%20had%20%E2%80%9Ca%20reasonable%20nexus%20with%20the%20objectives%E2%80%9D%20like%20eradicating%20black%20marketing%2C%20terror%20funding%2C%20etc.%20that%20it%20sought%20to%20achieve.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20relevant%20whether%20the%20objective%20was%20achieved%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fdemonetisation-will-not-eliminate-black-money-or-corruption%5C%22%3EWhy%20Demonetisation%20Will%20Not%20Eliminate%20Black%20Money%20or%20Corruption%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20economist%20Pronab%20Sen%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20demonetisation%20had%20%E2%80%9Cpenalised%20virtually%20the%20entire%20informal%20sector%2C%20and%20perhaps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fmodis-demonetisation-move-may-have-permanently-damaged-indias-informal-sector%5C%22%3Edamaged%20it%20permanently%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20a%20year%20after%20demonetisation%2C%20RBI%20data%20showed%20that%20Rs%2015.28%20lakh%20crore%20out%20of%20the%20Rs%2015.44%20lakh%20crore%20in%20currency%20that%20was%20rendered%20invalid%20on%20November%208%2C%202016%20had%20come%20back%20into%20the%20Indian%20banking%20system.%20This%20implied%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fdemonetisation-99-of-scrapped-notes-came-back-into-system%5C%22%3E98.96%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%20and%20Rs%20500%20notes%20that%20were%20banned%20as%20a%20result%20of%20demonetisation%20were%20returned%20to%20the%20central%20bank%20by%20the%20end%20of%20June%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202018%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20also%20referred%20to%20this%20data%20in%20Parliament%20when%20it%20informed%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20that%20it%20has%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-economic-impacts-after-effects-demonetisation-lack-of-assessment%5C%22%3E%20not%20studied%20or%20assessed%20the%20%E2%80%98impacts%20and%20after-effects%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20demonetisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22publishe