eme%E2%80%99s%20validity%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20and%20the%2030th%20batch%20sold%20since%20the%20scheme%20was%20launched%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20(SBI%E2%80%99s)%20reply%20to%20Batra%E2%80%99s%20query%2C%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%205%2C71%2C80%2C03%2C000%20have%20been%20sold%20across%20SBI%20branches%20in%20Bangalore%2C%20Chennai%2C%20Gandhinagar%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20Visakhapatnam%2C%20Mumbai%20and%20Jaipur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%20897%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20sold%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%2C%20Rs%2010%2C000%2C%20Rs%201%20lakh%20and%20Rs%201%20crore%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20415%2C%20or%20nearly%20half%2C%20have%20been%20sold%20in%20Kolkata.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20maximum%20number%20of%20bonds%20(540)%20have%20been%20sold%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20with%20161%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20followed%20by%20Hyderabad%20(131)%20and%20Chennai%20(73).%20The%20money%20mobilised%20thorough%20bonds%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20make%20up%20for%2094.4%25%20of%20the%20total%20money%20in%20circulation%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20this%20phase.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F16751303%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F16751303%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F16751303%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlmost%2092%25%20of%20the%20bonds%20sold%20in%20this%20period%20have%20been%20encashed%20with%20only%2025%20bonds%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20and%20Rs%201%20lakh%20left%20unused.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20phase%20of%20bond%20sale%20is%20expected%20to%20happen%20in%20February%20or%20March.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EControversy%20surrounding%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20came%20under%20the%20scanner%20soon%20after%20it%20was%20launched%20for%20being%20opaque%20and%20possibly%20routing%20unaccounted%20money%20to%20political%20parties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20last%20round%20of%20electoral%20bond%20sales%20were%20announced%20two%20days%20after%20the%20apex%20court%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20November%202%2C%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EActivists%20have%20also%20pointed%20out%20the%20substantial%20six-year%20gap%20between%20the%20first%20petition%20challenging%20the%20scheme%2C%20filed%20in%202017%2C%20and%20the%20case%20being%20heard%20by%20a%20constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20only%20in%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20hearings%2C%20the%20government%20pleaded%20to%20protect%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20big%20corporate%20donors%20to%20political%20parties%20with%20Attorney%20General%20R.%20Venkataramani%20going%20as%20far%20as%20to%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcitizens-have-no-fundamental-right-to-know-of-source-of-political-funding-ag-to-sc%5C%22%3Ethat%20citizens%20have%20no%20fundamental%20right%20to%20know%20the%20sources%20of%20electoral%20bond%20funds.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20donors%20is%20exempt%20from%20RTIs%2C%20concerns%20have%20been%20raised%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20might%20be%20able%20to%20access%20data%20of%20a%20publi